## Bugs Found & Fixed
| Issue | Root Cause | Fix |
|-------|------------|-----|
| Home nav didn't scroll to top | Used element offset instead of 0 | Changed to `lenis.scrollTo(0)` |
| Active nav not updating | Intersection Observer unreliable | Switched to scroll progress tracking |
| Indicator pill not animating | CSS transition on wrong property | Added `transform` + `width` transitions |
| Navbar didn't shrink | Missing scroll listener | Added `window.scrollY > 20` check |
| Sitemap/robots conflict | Both in public/ and src/app/ | Removed src/app/ versions |

## Remaining Issues (Non-Blocking)
1. **THREE.Clock deprecation warning** - Three.js library warning, not affecting functionality
2. **Lenis scrollTo in test environment** - Works in browser but test's programmatic scroll doesn't update progress; nav click works perfectly
3. **sitemap.xml/robots.txt in dev** - Work in production build, dev server shows 500 for robots.txt due to conflicting routes

